# Implementation Plan: Sprint 001 - Core Task API

Establish the foundational REST API for MicroTaskManager using FastAPI and SQLite, adhering to the discovery-first principles and quality gates.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This plan assumes a clean environment. We will initialize the project with `pyproject.toml` (using `ruff`, `mypy`, `pylint`, `pytest`) and create the initial database migration.

## Proposed Changes

### [MicroTaskManager Core]
Summary of the initial API structure.

#### [NEW] [main.py](file:///c:/Users/Glauber/codes/MicroTaskManager/main.py)
Entry point for the FastAPI application.

#### [NEW] [database.py](file:///c:/Users/Glauber/codes/MicroTaskManager/database.py)
SQLite connection handling and schema initialization.

#### [NEW] [models.py](file:///c:/Users/Glauber/codes/MicroTaskManager/models.py)
SQLAlchemy models for Task (id, title, status, created_at, completed_at, due_at).

#### [NEW] [schemas.py](file:///c:/Users/Glauber/codes/MicroTaskManager/schemas.py)
Pydantic schemas for API request/response validation.

#### [NEW] [tests/test_tasks.py](file:///c:/Users/Glauber/codes/MicroTaskManager/tests/test_tasks.py)
Initial TDD suite for task CRUD operations.

